         <abstract>
            <p>We study the accuracy of the output of the Fast Fourier Transform by estimating the expected value and the variance of the accompanying linear forms in terms of the expected value and variance of the relative roundoff errors for the elementary operations of addition and multiplication. We compare the results with the corresponding ones for the direct algorithm for the Discrete Fourier Transform, and we give indications of the relative performances when different rounding schemes are used. We also present the results of numerical experiments run to test the theoretical bounds and discuss their significance.</p>
          </abstract>
